main event: Four unidentified objects were observed in East Rochester, New Hampshire on September 19, 1956.
interesting points: The objects were described as circular and white., The observation lasted for forty-five seconds., Witnesses reported the objects formed a straight line and then a square., One object faded out and one more appeared before fading out as well., The conclusion suggested they could be balloons or possibly aircraft.
witness description: Civilian observer looking out the window
